                            <comment id="15200128" author="vrodionov" created="Thu, 17 Mar 2016 18:35:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moved to Phase 3.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15317621" author="vrodionov" created="Tue, 7 Jun 2016 01:25:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Dangerous for operations which are not idempotent (Increment, Append)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15319245" author="enis" created="Tue, 7 Jun 2016 19:59:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Duplicate KVs having the same seqId is not an issue. We have the same behavior in replication (where replication can end up writing more than once). &lt;br/&gt;
Increment and Append are user-level operations. The WAL and HFile never contain non-idempotent operations like Increment. Both does a get + put, and the Put is written to the WAL, not an &quot;Increment&quot; operation. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15319416" author="vrodionov" created="Tue, 7 Jun 2016 21:02:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Did not know that. Thanks, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=enis&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;enis&quot;&gt;Enis Soztutar&lt;/a&gt;. Should I close this JIRA?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15321229" author="vrodionov" created="Wed, 8 Jun 2016 19:01:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Not the issue, according to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=enis&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;enis&quot;&gt;Enis Soztutar&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
